<item>
<title>Singapore says helping French with Olympic payment probe</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/sport/singapore-says-helping/2782256.html</link><description>French investigators say two payments were made by Japan's Olympic bid team to an account held by Black Tidings, a Singapore-based company linked to Papa Diack, son of disgraced athletics supremo Lamine Diack.</description><category>AFP Sports</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 06:31:57 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Japan to 'confirm facts' over Olympic payment claim</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/japan-to-confirm-facts/2782090.html</link><description>The Guardian newspaper reported on Wednesday that the Tokyo 2020 Olympic bid team had paid €1.3 million (US$1.48 million) as part of its efforts to host the Summer Games.</description><category>AFP Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 05:22:46 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Humble tofu powering Indonesian homes with clean energy</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/humble-tofu-powering/2781898.html</link><description>Tofu has been cooked this way for generations but today, innovative villagers on Java island are producing something extra from the simple soybean - cheap, renewable energy, piped directly into their homes.</description><category>AFP Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 05:48:20 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>By-election date for 2 Malaysian towns set following death of two MPs</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/by-election-date-for-2/2782020.html</link><description>Two members of parliament died on May 5 after a helicopter crashed in Sarawak.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 04:38:13 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Malaysia says four missing at sea found on trespassing Vietnam trawler</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/malaysia-says-four/2781994.html</link><description>The quartet were unexpectedly discovered Thursday when a Vietnamese fishing trawler was intercepted in the disputed Spratly Islands near Layang-Layang atoll, a popular diving spot, </description><category>AFP Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 04:30:37 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Canberra probes death of Australian contractor at Iraq embassy</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/canberra-probes-death-of/2782010.html</link><description>Australia said on Friday it was investigating the death of an Australian security contractor at its embassy in the Iraqi capital, following reports of a shootout.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 04:10:11 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Malaysia's economy grew 4.2% in Q1, slowest in 6 years</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/malaysia-s-economy-grew-4/2781980.html</link><description>This is the slowest growth the country's economy has experienced since the third quarter of 2009. </description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 04:47:23 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>New Myanmar government proposes keeping some junta curbs on protests</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/new-myanmar-government-pr/2781974.html</link><description>Myanmar democracy champion Aung San Suu Kyi is facing criticism from rights groups and student activists who say her ruling party is planning to retain restrictions on free speech once wielded against it by the country's former junta.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 04:30:14 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>China, US should manage Sth China Sea differences constructively - Chinese general</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/china-us-should-manage/2781724.html</link><description>China and the United States should manage their differences over disputed waters in the South China Sea constructively, one of China's top military officials has said.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 05:35:07 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Challenge to Australia's Senate voting reforms rejected in boost for PM Turnbull</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/challenge-to-australia-s/2781626.html</link><description>Australia's High Court rejected a challenge to reforms to Senate voting on Friday in a boost for Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull ahead of elections on July 2.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 01:25:13 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Philippines' cash-strapped cops cheer new crime-buster president</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/philippines-cash-strapped/2781514.html</link><description>The police force in Manila is so underfunded that officers say they have to buy their own bullets and it is not uncommon for funeral service cars to give cops a lift along to murder scenes because they have no vehicles of their own.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 00:49:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Japan, US preparing summit meeting around May 25: Government sources</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/japan-us-preparing-summit/2781500.html</link><description>Japan and the United States are preparing to hold a summit meeting around May 25, government sources told Reuters on Friday.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 04:28:09 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Thailand's opposition muted ahead of referendum</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/thailand-s-opposition/2781460.html</link><description>In northeast Thailand, once a hotbed of opposition to Thailand's junta, troops patrol university campuses in Humvees and hold "attitude adjustment sessions" at military camps for those who don't toe the line.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2016 00:00:20 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Japanese billionaire mystery buyer of Basquiat painting</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/japanese-billionaire/2781364.html</link><description>A Japanese billionaire is the mystery art collector behind the US$57.3 million purchase of a huge self-portrait by Jean-Michel Basquiat at auction earlier this week, his art foundation said on Thursday.</description><category>AFP Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 22:56:21 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>US congratulates Philippines' Duterte, wants to deepen ties</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/us-congratulates/2781204.html</link><description>The United States congratulated the Philippines' "presumptive" President-elect Rodrigo Duterte on Thursday and said it looked forward to deepening US-Philippine ties with his incoming administration.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 22:09:23 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Artist Ai Weiwei says Gaza key part of refugee crisis</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/artist-ai-weiwei-says/2780624.html</link><description>Chinese dissident artist Ai Weiwei said on Thursday he felt compelled to visit Gaza to understand its part in the global refugee crisis for a documentary he is filming.</description><category>AFP World</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 17:10:07 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Indonesia protests against Singapore's move to 'interrogate' company director</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/indonesia-protests/2780446.html</link><description>On Wednesday, Singapore's National Environment Agency said it had obtained a court warrant after the director failed to heed the Transboundary Haze Pollution Act notice served to him by NEA when he was in Singapore.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 16:23:05 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Nepal says needs more aid for quake rebuilding</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/nepal-says-needs-more-aid/2780546.html</link><description>Aid-dependent Nepal needs US$7.86 billion over five years, US$1.17 billion more than earlier estimates, to rebuild homes and infrastructure destroyed by the deadly earthquake in 2015, the government said on Thursday.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 15:25:19 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Malaysia PM stresses unity at UMNO 70th anniversary celebrations</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/malaysia-pm-stresses/2780252.html</link><description>Malaysian Prime Minister Najib Razak swore he would never betray or abandon the party, even if he were to have "misunderstandings" with his successor someday. </description><category>AFP Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 18:50:52 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Row deepens between Pakistan, Bangladesh over executed Islamist leader</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/row-deepens-between-pakis/2780166.html</link><description>Pakistan and Bangladesh summoned each other's ambassadors on Thursday to register "strong protest" in connection with a row over the execution of an Islamist leader in Bangladesh this week, both sides said in statements.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 13:30:16 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Duterte wants to open Philippines to foreign investors: Aide</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/duterte-wants-to-open/2779914.html</link><description>Foreign entities cannot own more than 40 per cent equity in certain businesses, including those requiring franchises granted by parliament, such as aviation and telecommunications.</description><category>AFP Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 12:53:42 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Suicide bombing in Nigeria's Maiduguri kills at least four people - residents</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/suicide-bombing-in/2779908.html</link><description>A suicide bombing at a government compound in the northeastern Nigerian city of Maiduguri killed at least five people and wounded 19 on Thursday, residents and hospital workers said.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 12:35:11 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>A look back: Life in Malaysia scorched by El Nino</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/a-look-back-life-in/2779070.html</link><description>As hot and dry weather gives way to cool and wet climate, Channel NewsAsia looks back at how El Nino has impacted the lives of Malaysian residents.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 12:06:47 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Indonesia tells 78 names mentioned in 'Panama Papers' to correct tax reports</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/indonesia-tells-78-names/2779264.html</link><description>The head of the tax office Ken Dwijugiasteadi told a news press conference that the Panama Papers mentioned 1,010 Indonesian people and 28 firms as having set up shell companies abroad.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 09:29:12 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>4 people missing off Sabah for 10 days found alive</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/4-people-missing-off/2779094.html</link><description>The Malaysian Maritime Enforcement Agency says the four people whose boat went missing off Sabah last week have been found after a 10-day search off the northern tip of Sabah.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 11:13:37 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Mao's influence lingers 50 years after China's Cultural Revolution</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/mao-s-influence-lingers/2779006.html</link><description>Fifty years after the Cultural Revolution spread bloodshed and turmoil across China, the Communist-ruled country is driving firmly down the capitalist road, but Mao Zedong's legacy remains - like the embalmed leader himself - far from buried.</description><category>AFP Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 08:18:57 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>British 'barbarians' need manners lesson, says China paper</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/british-barbarians-need/2778592.html</link><description>The British media is riddled with "barbarians" who would benefit from a lesson in manners from China's ancient civilisation, a state-run newspaper said on Thursday after Queen Elizabeth II called some Chinese officials "very rude".</description><category>AFP Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 08:08:40 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Tourists jump for their lives from burning Australia boat</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/tourists-jump-for-their/2778944.html</link><description>The Spirit of 1770 got into trouble 10 nautical miles off the coastal town of 1770 following a day-trip to Lady Musgrave Island on the Great Barrier Reef, apparently when a fire started in the engine room.</description><category>AFP Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 08:02:21 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Myanmar parliament calls for halt to Parkway hospital project in Yangon</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/myanmar-parliament-calls/2778716.html</link><description>The US$70-million, 250-bed hospital broke ground in January this year, and was to be developed and operated by a joint venture consortium comprising majority shareholder Parkway Healthcare Indo-China. </description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 13:08:39 GMT</pubDate></item><item>
<title>Vietnam says would welcome US accelerating lifting of arms ban</title>
<link>http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/vietnam-says-would/2778718.html</link><description>Vietnam would welcome the United States "accelerating" the lifting of a lethal arms embargo, which would reflect trust between the two countries and recognition of its needs to defend itself, its foreign ministry said on Thursday.</description><category>Asia Pacific</category><pubDate>Thu, 12 May 2016 08:24:07 GMT</pubDate></item></channel>
</rss>
